c.)`\n- This is wrapped by `SchemeBuilder` and `AddToScheme` to register the types\n\nThe registration chain flows through:\n1. `addKnownTypes()` in core/v1/register.go - registers all core/v1 types\n2. `metav1.AddToGroupVersion()` in staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/register.go (lines 66-86) - registers metav1 types like WatchEvent and Status\n3. Ultimately calls into `Scheme.AddKnownTypes()` in staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/scheme.go\n\n## DeepCopyObject Implementation\nThe `DeepCopyObject()` method required by runtime.Object is auto-generated in `staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` for metav1 types, and similar generated files exist for all core/v1 types.\n\n## Import Chain Summary\n- Core API types import metav1 types from k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\n- metav1 types import runtime types from k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\n- The registration system connects all these types to the Scheme for serialization and deserialization\n- All core/v1 resources in `staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/` implement runtime.Object through the TypeMeta and ObjectMeta embedding pattern\n"
